Anger over poor service delivery is spilling onto the streets once again. This time, residents in the capital Tshwane, say they've had enough of high electricity prices and dirty drinking water, among other issues. Courtesy #DStv403 TSHWANE - Residents of Tshwane have made their way to the Union Buildings on Monday to protest poor service delivery. The protest was planned to bring the city to a standstill, however, only about a hundred demonstrators arrived to air their grievances on Monday afternoon. READ: Tshwane in the grip of service delivery protests Residents are calling for better service delivery, lower electricity rates and clean drinking water. The people stated they would not be voting until they receive better services. Other protestors called for a standard electricity rate and no further price hikes on petrol.